args:
Gatov guides the party to the Grams slums,
where they discuss the situation. And while
Gatov promises to take the prince to the Faerie
Kingdom, he urges him think long and hard on
whether or not he truly wishes to go there.
Oh, what beautiful clothes...\nWhere do those people come from?
Hell if I know—and it's got nothin' to do\nwith the likes of us! Best keep your eyes\npointed at the dirt and not the stars.

A place filled with those who lack family,
employment, or coin—and sometimes
all three. It is an area of Grams known
simply as ＂the slums.＂
Hard to imagine we're just a stone's throw\naway from that gorgeous cityscape.
What is the Church doing? Will they not\ngrant aid to these downtrodden citizens?
I, too, was shocked when I first came to\ntown and laid eyes upon this sight.
Grams is a rich land, yes, but one beset\nalso by terrible poverty and social inequity.
But let us speak again on the intricacies of\nthis place if the opportunity presents itself.
For now, come this way and I will\nshow you to our headquarters.

Forgive me for the cramped space, but
there is no fear of being overheard here.
Now then, it is good to see you all have
come to Grams.
By all rights I should have come to you,\nbut I fear I've been forced into various\ndifficult situations of late.
Please don't apologize. Without you,\nwe'd likely be rotting away in some\nTemplar prison right now.
Ah, it was but a trifle. More importantly,\nI finally get to meet the two of you,\nChelle and {player_name}!
Aurelius's pride in his children was always\nevident in his letters to me.
Tell me, Gatov: What was the nature\nof your relationship with my father?

We had our share of happenings when I
was a young lad. Aurelius was a brother in
arms—or perhaps better to say a partner
in crime! Aaaah ha ha ha ha!

Yes, well, it was some time back when
last we saw each other in person;
your brother Leonidas was still practically
a babe in the cradle.

I had no words when I learned of your
father's sudden passing. I heard he fell in
battle with the Other, and I lamented my
failure to aid him.
But what I can do now is honor and protect\nthe promise I made to him in life.
As you likely surmise, young prince,\nI am to escort you to the Faerie Kingdom.
Have you ever visited the\nFaerie Kingdom, Gatov?
Yes, though it was a number of years ago.\nAs such, I know the method to get there.
What the hey does that mean?
The location of the kingdom is hidden\nby a special art of the faeries.
You must undo the seal to have any hope\nof entering the place.
Sounds like it's a good thing we have\nyou to show us the way then, Gatov.
Of course. However, before we do that,\nI want to confirm that you are indeed\ndetermined to see this thing done.
What do you mean? Of course I am.
I'm doing this for Leonidas, as well as the\nfriends who accompanied me all this way.
It's praiseworthy to think of your comrades\nlike that, but this is a journey for you—\nand all that matters is what YOU want.
If you go to the Faerie Kingdom,\nyou may well face a painful reality.
This reality may well shatter the values\nand ways of thinking that you have\ncultivated all this time.
Think carefully about whether or not you\ntruly have the resolve to endure that.
If you think you will not be able to,\nthere is no shame in fleeing.
As I said, you needn't be ashamed.\nIt is simply another option.

I suspect you will not have an immediate
answer—and while I would love to give
you time to think about it, we will not
be safe in this place for long.
For the time being, I will guide you\nto the forest in the north.
And what is in this forest?
Entering the forest is the first step\nto undoing the faerie arts.
In fact, I have already sent people\nfor initial scouting and preparations.
Until we get there, young prince, you\nshould harden your resolve as to what\nyour course of action is going to be.
Once we reach the woods,\nit will be difficult to turn back.
Forgive me for interrupting, Captain,\nbut it is time.
Sorry, all, but I'm afraid I have\na watch meeting to attend.
There have been some enigmatic fiends\nshowing up near Grams lately, and we\nneed to sort out countermeasures.
We will depart as soon as I return.\nPlease wait here until then.
We will be ready to leave the moment\nyou return, Gatov. Thank you.
